565
01:10:10,730 --> 01:10:12,720
She's the daughter of Xebel.

566
01:10:12,770 --> 01:10:16,670
If any harm befalls her,
our coalition is over.

567
01:10:16,700 --> 01:10:20,940
Your Highness, we are now entering
the waters of the Fisherman Kingdom.

568
01:10:20,940 --> 01:10:27,750
Securing the alliance of the other two
kingdoms should be our immediate concern.

569
01:10:29,980 --> 01:10:32,820
My vizier is correct.

570
01:10:33,720 --> 01:10:35,750
As usual.

571
01:10:36,820 --> 01:10:43,750
Arrest them and bring back King Nereus's
daughter unharmed.

572
01:11:05,950 --> 01:11:07,110
We're here.

573
01:11:09,090 --> 01:11:11,990
Hey, is there anything nearby?

574
01:11:11,990 --> 01:11:14,960
Nothing but deserts for hundreds
of… mate.- Nothing but deserts…

575
01:11:15,000 --> 01:11:15,990
He's wrong!

576
01:11:18,070 --> 01:11:19,120
Mera, no!

577
01:11:22,040 --> 01:11:24,060
She just jumped without a parachute.

578
01:11:24,100 --> 01:11:27,040
Redhead. You gotta love 'em.

579
01:11:56,100 --> 01:11:58,100
You're crazier than I thought.

580
01:12:00,910 --> 01:12:01,970
This way.

581
01:12:23,160 --> 01:12:27,100
You were defeated the last time because
your surface weapons failed you.

582
01:12:27,130 --> 01:12:29,160
Ours will not.

583
01:12:32,040 --> 01:12:36,030
It's prototype armour for the next
generation Atlantean soldier.

584
01:12:36,210 --> 01:12:39,940
Revenge is something we
Atlantean understand.

585
01:12:39,950 --> 01:12:43,080
You will lead my finest
commandoes as your personal army,

586
01:12:43,080 --> 01:12:45,140
to hunt the half breed abomination.

587
01:12:45,190 --> 01:12:48,050
I can't touch them but you can.

588
01:12:48,090 --> 01:12:49,990
He's fled to your world.

589
01:12:49,990 --> 01:12:51,980
Kill him and the woman he's with

590
01:12:52,030 --> 01:12:53,150
and you will be rewarded.

591
01:12:53,190 --> 01:12:56,030
Killing him is my reward.

592
01:12:59,100 --> 01:13:02,900
The crown jewel is too experimental.

593
01:13:03,070 --> 01:13:06,100
Converge water into beams
of energised plasma.

594
01:14:19,110 --> 01:14:21,750
Hmm, I think we're gonna
need a bigger helmet.

595
01:14:21,750 --> 01:14:26,390
One of the tribes of Atlantis broke off and settled
here when the region was still an inland sea.

596
01:14:26,420 --> 01:14:29,360
When the water dried up,
they perished along with it.

597
01:14:29,360 --> 01:14:31,320
Perished? Yeah that's great.

598
01:14:31,330 --> 01:14:33,390
We're getting close now.-
Yeah, close to what?

599
01:14:33,390 --> 01:14:35,450
Dying of thirst?- I'm close
to punching your face.

600
01:14:35,500 --> 01:14:38,360
A fight club? I didn't know you knew
how things work up here.

601
01:14:38,370 --> 01:14:40,300
Why don;t you look around, we are lost.

602
01:14:40,330 --> 01:14:43,330
You see that over there.
What is that? Na-da.

603
01:14:43,340 --> 01:14:44,360
This place's a wasteland.

604
01:14:44,510 --> 01:14:47,340
You're the one who call this
'wasteland' a home.

605
01:14:47,380 --> 01:14:48,570
This isn't my home.

606
01:14:48,610 --> 01:14:51,310
The whole shore doesn't look like this.

607
01:14:51,310 --> 01:14:52,440
Oh, no. Of course not.

608
01:14:52,480 --> 01:14:56,320
You also got disgusting cities with sewers
emptying out into our ocean

609
01:14:56,350 --> 01:14:57,580
and whole mountains made out of thrash.

610
01:14:57,590 --> 01:15:01,550
You got great factories, and…

611
01:15:01,560 --> 01:15:03,520
Ok, ok, ok. Point taken. Listen.

612
01:15:03,560 --> 01:15:06,430
Yeah, we got some idiots running the show.
But there are good things too right.

613
01:15:06,430 --> 01:15:08,420
We got green forest, big mountains,

614
01:15:08,430 --> 01:15:09,400
and beautiful lakes.

615
01:15:09,430 --> 01:15:13,330
You'd love them. There are like baby
oceans.- Are you trying to provoke me?

616
01:15:13,330 --> 01:15:15,530
I'm just trying to say don't judge
a place before you even see it.

617
01:15:15,540 --> 01:15:17,560
You judged Atlantis on far less.

618
01:15:21,580 --> 01:15:24,440
No, no, no. Will you
just stop it with that.

619
01:15:24,480 --> 01:15:25,540
No.

620
01:15:25,550 --> 01:15:28,540
Your stupid Atlantean GPS just told you to
jump out of an airplane

621
01:15:28,580 --> 01:15:31,450
over the middle of the desert.
And now we are stranded.

622
01:15:34,520 --> 01:15:37,460
If you are the next
true king we're doomed.

623
01:16:05,320 --> 01:16:06,450
That was awesome.

624
01:16:12,560 --> 01:16:15,330
Look what I found.

625
01:16:15,330 --> 01:16:18,300
What you found?- Yeah.

626
01:16:28,310 --> 01:16:29,570
Check this place out.

627
01:16:30,380 --> 01:16:33,350
This is badass!

628
01:16:33,550 --> 01:16:39,380
This is the hall of armoury where the legend
says where Atlann's Trident was forged.

629
01:16:41,320 --> 01:16:43,380
I don't think they are a legend anymore.

630
01:16:49,360 --> 01:16:51,490
I was right.

631
01:16:53,370 --> 01:16:55,360
It's real.

632
01:17:33,540 --> 01:17:35,480
Nothing.

633
01:17:35,480 --> 01:17:37,570
Of course it's not working.
It's been sitting here

634
01:17:37,610 --> 01:17:40,340
collecting dust since before
the Sahara was a desert.

635
01:17:41,520 --> 01:17:47,390
Man.- Since before the Sahara
was a desert.

636
01:17:47,390 --> 01:17:49,450
Thank you for repeating what I just said.

637
01:17:49,490 --> 01:17:51,480
It's completely dried out.

638
01:17:53,460 --> 01:17:56,450
You do the best thinking when
you're not thinking at all.

639
01:17:56,460 --> 01:17:58,490
Now hold still.

640
01:17:58,500 --> 01:18:01,400
What are you doing?- We need water.

641
01:18:01,540 --> 01:18:05,560
You are the closest source.
Now hold still.

642
01:18:43,540 --> 01:18:45,480
We could've just peed on it.

643
01:18:55,490 --> 01:18:57,390
King Atlann.

644
01:18:59,390 --> 01:19:04,330
In this Trident resides
the power of Atlantis.

645
01:19:04,370 --> 01:19:08,500
In the wrong hands, it
would bring destruction.

646
01:19:08,500 --> 01:19:12,440
In the hands of the true heir,
it will unite all our

647
01:19:12,470 --> 01:19:14,470
kingdoms above and below.

648
01:19:14,480 --> 01:19:19,350
If you seek my power,
you must prove your worth.

649
01:19:19,380 --> 01:19:23,280
Journey beyond the edge of
the world to the hidden sea.

650
01:19:23,320 --> 01:19:26,380
Look inside the bottle
for the chartered path.

651
01:19:26,390 --> 01:19:29,380
Only in the hands of the true king,

652
01:19:29,420 --> 01:19:32,420
can he truly see.

653
01:19:47,470 --> 01:19:49,570
We can't let Orm find this.

654
01:19:51,510 --> 01:19:53,380
Hey, wait! No…

655
01:19:54,380 --> 01:19:55,470
What?

656
01:19:55,480 --> 01:19:57,450
Shouldn't we have written it down first?

657
01:19:57,480 --> 01:20:00,420
I memorised it. Didn't you?

658
01:20:01,460 --> 01:20:03,320
Oh, yeah.

659
01:20:03,560 --> 01:20:05,530
What did it just said?

660
01:20:07,490 --> 01:20:10,360
Something something Trident.

661
01:20:32,590 --> 01:20:35,320
It's our next stop.

662
01:22:09,350 --> 01:22:11,510
I'm starting to think you actually
like the surface dwellers.

663
01:22:11,520 --> 01:22:14,450
It'd be wrong to judge a place
I've never seen before.

664
01:22:16,360 --> 01:22:19,380
I'll be right back. Don't go anywhere.

665
01:22:39,410 --> 01:22:41,580
Well, apparently she's right up on the
hill in the old castle.

666
01:22:41,580 --> 01:22:44,520
I've just learnt something
very interesting.

667
01:22:45,420 --> 01:22:47,290
Pinocchio.

668
01:22:47,420 --> 01:22:50,450
You risk our lives on something you read
on a children's book?

669
01:22:51,490 --> 01:22:55,290
Wait it's a book? How about that.

670
01:22:55,560 --> 01:22:59,330
We have to go.

671
01:23:03,500 --> 01:23:07,530
King Nereus, I had hoped
that our people had evolved

672
01:23:07,570 --> 01:23:10,570
that war with the surface is inevitable.

673
01:23:10,610 --> 01:23:16,410
It is the position of the Fishermen that
when the time comes to make ourselves known

674
01:23:16,420 --> 01:23:17,480
to the lands men.

675
01:23:17,480 --> 01:23:19,420
It shall be to educate them,

676
01:23:19,590 --> 01:23:21,560
not destroy them.

677
01:23:21,690 --> 01:23:25,520
I admire your lofty aspirations King…

678
01:23:28,530 --> 01:23:33,590
But I suspect they are a cloud of
ink hiding the heart of coward

679
01:23:33,600 --> 01:23:35,470
How dare you!

680
01:23:37,570 --> 01:23:40,560
Please, I implore you.

681
01:23:40,570 --> 01:23:44,600
Your kingdom's bloated
philosophers and flaccid moments

682
01:23:44,610 --> 01:23:48,410
whose waters have gone
stagnant and it sickens me.

683
01:23:56,560 --> 01:23:57,580
My king!

684
01:23:57,620 --> 01:23:59,460
The king is dead.

685
01:23:59,660 --> 01:24:02,460
Long live the heir.

686
01:24:03,530 --> 01:24:08,590
Princess. Prepare your
armies, Your Highness.

687
01:24:08,600 --> 01:24:12,400
We move against the Brine kingdom at once.

688
01:24:20,450 --> 01:24:21,640
What are the records saying again?

689
01:24:21,680 --> 01:24:25,580
Journey beyond the edge of
the world to the hidden sea.

690
01:24:25,590 --> 01:24:27,580
Look into the bottle for
the chartered path.

691
01:24:27,620 --> 01:24:29,610
Only in the hands of the true king,

692
01:24:29,620 --> 01:24:31,590
can he truly see.

693
01:24:33,560 --> 01:24:36,620
Look into the bottle for
the chartered path.

694
01:24:40,700 --> 01:24:44,660
Oh man.- What?

695
01:24:50,610 --> 01:24:53,480
But how do you know where
to point it…- Let me see.

696
01:24:53,480 --> 01:24:54,570
What's the last line?

697
01:24:54,610 --> 01:24:57,380
Only in the hands of the true king,

698
01:24:57,420 --> 01:24:58,540
can he truly see.

699
01:25:03,560 --> 01:25:05,650
He was a great General,
but he wasn't a king.

700
01:25:10,600 --> 01:25:14,560
How do you know all this stuff?- My pops.
He make sure I know my history.

701
01:25:14,600 --> 01:25:19,670
None of these guys are
kings, except this guy.

702
01:25:19,670 --> 01:25:22,580
Romulos, first king of Rome.

703
01:25:24,480 --> 01:25:26,570
Only in the hands of the true king,

704
01:25:26,610 --> 01:25:28,510
can he truly see.

705
01:25:37,590 --> 01:25:41,590
There it is. That's where we're heading.-
What? Let me see.

706
01:25:48,470 --> 01:25:50,560
Not bad, for an imbecile huh?

707
01:25:51,670 --> 01:25:54,470
Not bad at all.

708
01:30:56,450 --> 01:30:58,280
Go!

709
01:31:08,460 --> 01:31:12,360
I'll show you the same mercy
you showed my father.

710
01:31:12,400 --> 01:31:15,330
And cut you like the fish you are.

711
01:33:10,310 --> 01:33:12,370
Arthur!

712
01:33:15,290 --> 01:33:19,310
Mera. They are tracking you.- What?

713
01:33:19,360 --> 01:33:22,230
They are tracking you.

714
01:33:31,440 --> 01:33:35,430
Arthur! Stay with me.

715
01:33:35,440 --> 01:33:38,310
Arthur, wake up.

716
01:34:30,260 --> 01:34:32,290
Did you steal a boat?

717
01:34:32,300 --> 01:34:35,270
Are the boats at the
marina not for public use?

718
01:34:35,270 --> 01:34:38,430
No. Those belong to people.

719
01:34:41,440 --> 01:34:45,240
Those are Orm's elite commandoes.
The one who lead them

720
01:34:45,240 --> 01:34:50,380
isn't Atlantean. I've never
seen him before.- Yeah, I have.

721
01:34:51,320 --> 01:34:54,180
He and his father were pirates.

722
01:34:54,220 --> 01:34:57,420
He blames me for his father's death.

723
01:34:57,460 --> 01:35:02,450
He pick a dangerous line of trade.
It's not your fault.

724
01:35:02,460 --> 01:35:06,260
It's not how I feels.

725
01:35:06,300 --> 01:35:09,320
It was up to me, I let him die,

726
01:35:10,400 --> 01:35:13,340
I could save him but I didn't.

727
01:35:13,340 --> 01:35:19,370
I know I made an enemy. And he could
hurt you, knowing it's my fault.

728
01:35:20,480 --> 01:35:22,470
Well he's behind us now.

729
01:35:24,350 --> 01:35:27,410
It's what lies ahead
that should concerns us.

730
01:35:28,350 --> 01:35:32,310
The chartered path leads to
the kingdom of the Trench.

731
01:35:33,420 --> 01:35:36,390
That's the same creatures
that killed my mother.

732
01:35:36,430 --> 01:35:40,230
Yes. She was taken there
and sacrificed to them.

733
01:35:40,230 --> 01:35:42,330
It has become a place of death.

734
01:35:42,370 --> 01:35:45,270
I know next to nothing
about what's down there.

735
01:35:48,370 --> 01:35:50,360
We should turn back.

736
01:35:50,510 --> 01:35:53,440
We can still warn the surface, try to
prepare them for what's coming.

737
01:35:53,440 --> 01:35:56,470
Turn back?
- Look. I learn from a young age

738
01:35:56,480 --> 01:35:59,210
about not to show weakness.

739
01:35:59,250 --> 01:36:02,220
Hey, it's not a problem
with my anger and my fist.

740
01:36:02,220 --> 01:36:05,190
I'm a blunt instrument
and I'm damn good at it.

741
01:36:05,220 --> 01:36:08,280
I've done nothing.
Getting my ass kicked

742
01:36:08,290 --> 01:36:09,450
this whole trip.

743
01:36:09,460 --> 01:36:13,260
I'm no leader. I'm not a king.

744
01:36:13,300 --> 01:36:15,430
I do not work or play well with others.

745
01:36:16,270 --> 01:36:18,290
And I”m not going to let you die

746
01:36:18,300 --> 01:36:20,430
trying to turn me into something I'm not.

747
01:36:21,270 --> 01:36:26,010
You think you're unworthy to lead because
we're from two different worlds.

748
01:36:26,140 --> 01:36:30,100
But that is exactly why you are worthy.

749
01:36:30,110 --> 01:36:33,980
You are the bridge between land and sea.

750
01:36:34,020 --> 01:36:36,180
I can see that now.

751
01:36:36,220 --> 01:36:42,130
The only question is, can you?

752
01:36:56,940 --> 01:37:00,970
The tracking on Lady Mera is still
dark, Your Highness.

753
01:37:00,980 --> 01:37:05,880
Vulko, my trusted vizier.

754
01:37:05,920 --> 01:37:09,750
You stood by the throne since my father.

755
01:37:10,950 --> 01:37:14,790
Have you any advise for
me since this war begins

756
01:37:14,790 --> 01:37:17,660
I've already given it, my king.

757
01:37:17,690 --> 01:37:20,890
That I will stand by
your decision as always.

758
01:37:20,930 --> 01:37:23,920
My decision…

759
01:37:23,930 --> 01:37:27,870
To protect it…

760
01:37:28,770 --> 01:37:30,930
